A part of the Murtala Muhammed International Airport, Lagos was on Wednesday gutted by fire. SaharaReporters gathered that the incident occurred at the departure hall of the Kenyan airways. Murtala Mohammed Intl. Airport Lagos
NAN The cause of the fire has yet to be ascertained as at press time. “Part of the Lagos airport was earlier gutted by fire. The Kenyan airways office at departure, that was where the fire happened. “The airport staff around quenched the fire alongside some fire fighters from FAAN (Federal Airports Authority of Nigeria),” a source told SaharaReporters.